 Here's a simple yet efficient way to reverse a string in JavaScript:

```javascript
function reverseString(str) {
  // Split the input string into an array of characters, reverse it and then join it back together
  return str.split('').reverse().join('');
}

// Example usage:
const exampleStr = "Hello, World!";
console.log(reverseString(exampleStr)); // Outputs: !dlroW ,olleH
```

